2011 ica summer film festival nora's will events at stanford 2011 ica summer film festival nora's will facebook twitter email print add to calendar nora's will mexico 2008 not rated 92 mins spanish no subtitles this story begins when jose finds out that nora the woman he d been married to for 30 years and then divorced has committed suicide the rabbi explains to jose that due to the celebration of the passover festivities together with a few other factors if nora is not buried that same day they will have to wait almost five days to be able to carry out the burial it turns out that before she died nora devised a machiavellian plan in order for him to take care of her funeral but she missed something a mysterious photograph left under the bed will lead to an unexpected outcome which will remind us that sometimes the greatest love stories are hidden in the smallest places in spanish with no subtitles when thursday august 11 2011 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where building 200 room 002 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags film other international arts sponsor center for latin american studies division of international comparative & area studies contact 650 725 0383 adoriala stanford edu admission free and open to public permalink http events stanford edu events 283 28351 more info last modified august 9 2011
